name: PARKA  VENUE / PARK A VENUE / PARK  AVENUE
description: What happens when we place an "A" in-between PARK & VENUE? Why, we get another BLG (Boomerang Letter Group) of course! PARKA VENUE becomes PARK A VENUE becomes PARK AVENUE and the letter can go back and forth between these words. The negative space between these words creates a type of asymmetry that's so soft and subtle. Almost as if saying to us, watch me play, watch me stray, and watch me slay. It's frozen and yet kinetic; an image of contradiction.
